Israeli Panel Recommends Raising Tax on Companies, High Earners

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   F e r z i g e r
-- 
2011-09-26T15:21:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/israeli-panel-recommends-raising-tax-on-companies-high-earners.html
An Israeli panel appointed by Prime
Minister  Benjamin Netanyahu  in response to popular protests over
the high cost of living recommended raising taxes on companies
and on individuals who earn more than about $129,000 a year. The
committee headed by economist Manuel Trajtenberg presented the
recommendations to Netanyahu today in  Jerusalem .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Ferziger in  Tel Aviv  at 
 jferziger@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Holland at 
 bholland1@bloomberg.net  